President Biden has declared a major disaster in West Virginia due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred in July 2022. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Jeffrey L. Jones has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional counties may receive assistance after the assessments are completed. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.